'''Cebeci İnönü Stadium''' ({{lang-tr|Cebeci İnönü Stadı}}) is a [[multi-purpose stadium]] in [[Ankara]], [[Turkey]]. It is currently used mostly for [[football (soccer)|football]] matches and was the home stadium of [[Hacettepespor]]. The stadium holds 15,000 people<ref name="tff">[http://www.tff.org/Default.aspx?pageID=394&stadID=13 "Cebeci İnönü Stadium."] [[Turkish Football Federation]]. 2009. {{tr icon}}</ref> and was built in 1967.<ref name="ws">[http://www.worldstadiums.com/middle_east/countries/turkey/central_anatolia.shtml World Stadiums: Cebeci İnönü Stadium] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130701064725/http://www.worldstadiums.com/middle_east/countries/turkey/central_anatolia.shtml |date=2013-07-01 }}</ref> It was named after the [[Turkish people|Turkish]] statesman [[İsmet İnönü]].

