This is a '''list of [[southpaw stance]] boxers'''. '''Southpaw''' is a [[boxing]] term that designates the stance where the boxer has his right hand and right foot forward, leading with right [[jab]]s, and following with a left [[cross (boxing)|cross]] right [[hook (boxing)|hook]]. Southpaw is the normal stance for a [[left-handed]] boxer. The corresponding designation for a right-handed boxer is [[orthodox (boxing)|orthodox]], and is generally a mirror-image of the southpaw stance.
