{{Infobox rugby team | teamname = Punjab Warriors | image = | fullname = | nickname = | location = [[Punjab, Pakistan|Punjab]], [[Pakistan]] | founded = 2011 | ground = | capacity = | coach = | captain = | league = | season = | position = | url = | pattern_la1=| pattern_b1=| pattern_ra1=| pattern_so1=| leftarm1=000| body1=000| rightarm1=000| shorts1=000| socks1=000| }}
The '''Punjab Warriors''' are a Pakistani [[Rugby union|rugby]] team. They play in the Pakistan Super XV League and serve as a Punjab select side under the jurisdiction of the [[Punjab Rugby Association]]. Presumably this team does not include players from [[Lahore Rugby Football Club|Lahore RFC]], as that club functions independently.
==History== Pakistan Warriors was founded in 2011 Adbul Rahim Khan. They squared off against powerhouses Lahore RFC in the Pakistan Super XV League played as part of the [[Azadi Cup (rugby)|Azadi Cup]], losing 5-20.<ref>[http://www.pakistantoday.com.pk/2011/10/03/news/sports/army-notch-azadi-cup-rugby-title/ Army notch Azadi Cup Rugby title]</ref> In January 2012 they faced the Indian side [[Delhi Sher RFC|Delhi Shers]] (formerly known as the Delhi Lions)<ref>[http://www.delhilions.com/about-delhi-shers About Delhi Shers] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120418012035/http://delhilions.com/about-delhi-shers |date=2012-04-18 }}</ref> who were on tour in Pakistan.
